#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:1
msgid "Release process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:3
msgid ""
"_Black_ has had a lot of work done into standardizing and automating its "
"release process. This document sets out to explain how everything works and "
"how to release _Black_ using said automation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:7
msgid "Release cadence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:9
msgid ""
"**We aim to release whatever is on `main` every 1-2 months.** This ensures "
"merged improvements and bugfixes are shipped to users reasonably quickly, "
"while not massively fracturing the user-base with too many versions. This "
"also keeps the workload on maintainers consistent and predictable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:14
msgid ""
"If there's not much new on `main` to justify a release, it's acceptable to "
"skip a month's release. Ideally January releases should not be skipped "
"because as per our [stability policy](labels/stability-policy), the first "
"release in a new calendar year may make changes to the _stable_ style. While "
"the policy applies to the first release (instead of only January releases), "
"confining changes to the stable style to January will keep things "
"predictable (and nicer) for users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:21
msgid ""
"Unless there is a serious regression or bug that requires immediate "
"patching, **there should not be more than one release per month**. While "
"version numbers are cheap, releases require a maintainer to both commit to "
"do the actual cutting of a release, but also to be able to deal with the "
"potential fallout post-release. Releasing more frequently than monthly nets "
"rapidly diminishing returns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:27
msgid "Cutting a release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:29
msgid ""
"**You must have `write` permissions for the _Black_ repository to cut a "
"release.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:31
msgid ""
"The 10,000 foot view of the release process is that you prepare a release PR "
"and then publish a [GitHub Release]. This triggers [release automation]"
"(#release-workflows) that builds all release artifacts and publishes them to "
"the various platforms we publish to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:35
msgid ""
"We now have a `scripts/release.py` script to help with cutting the release "
"PRs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:37
msgid "`python3 scripts/release.py --help` is your friend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:38
msgid ""
"`release.py` has only been tested in Python 3.12+ (so get with the times :D)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:40
msgid "To cut a release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:42
msgid "Determine the release's version number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:43
msgid ""
"**_Black_ follows the [CalVer] versioning standard using the `YY.M.N` "
"format**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:44
msgid ""
"So unless there already has been a release during this month, `N` should be "
"`0`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:45
msgid "Example: the first release in January, 2026 → `26.1.0`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:46
msgid ""
"`release.py` will calculate this and log it to stdout for your copy-paste "
"pleasure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:47
msgid ""
"Double-check that no changelog entries since the last release were put in "
"the wrong section (e.g., run `git diff origin/stable CHANGES.md`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:49
msgid ""
"File a PR editing `CHANGES.md` and the docs to version the latest changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:50
msgid "Run `python3 scripts/release.py [--debug]` to generate most changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:51
msgid "If `release.py` fails manually edit; otherwise, yay, skip this step!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:52
msgid "Replace the `## Unreleased` header with the version number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:53
msgid "Remove any empty sections for the current release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:54
msgid ""
"(_optional_) Read through and copy-edit the changelog (eg. by moving "
"entries, fixing typos, or rephrasing entries)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:56
msgid ""
"Update references to the latest version in {doc}`/integrations/"
"source_version_control` and {doc}`/usage_and_configuration/the_basics`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:59
msgid "Example PR: [GH-4563]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:60
msgid "Once the release PR is merged, wait until all CI passes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:61
msgid ""
"If CI does not pass, **stop** and investigate the failure(s) as generally "
"we'd want to fix failing CI before cutting a release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:63
msgid "[Draft a new GitHub Release][new-release]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:64
msgid ""
"Click `Choose a tag` and type in the version number, then select the `Create "
"new tag: YY.M.N on publish` option that appears"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:66
msgid "Verify that the new tag targets the `main` branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:67
msgid ""
"Make sure the release title is set to the version (`YY.M.N`), as otherwise "
"the default title is the last commit's title"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:69
msgid ""
"Copy and paste the _raw changelog Markdown_ for the current release into the "
"description box"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:71
msgid ""
"Publish the GitHub Release, triggering [release automation](#release-"
"workflows) that will handle the rest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:73
msgid ""
"Once CI is done add + PR a new empty template for the next release to "
"CHANGES.md _(Template is able to be copy pasted from release.py should we "
"fail)_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:75
msgid "`python3 scripts/release.py --add-changes-template|-a [--debug]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:76
msgid "Should that fail, please return to copy + paste"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:77
msgid ""
"At this point, you're basically done. It's good practice to go and [watch "
"and verify that all the release workflows pass][black-actions], although you "
"will receive a GitHub notification should something fail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:80
msgid ""
"If something fails, don't panic. Please go read the respective workflow's "
"logs and configuration file to reverse-engineer your way to a fix/solution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:83
msgid ""
"Congratulations! You've successfully cut a new release of _Black_. Go and "
"stand up and take a break, you deserve it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:87
msgid ""
"Once the release artifacts reach PyPI, you may see new issues being filed "
"indicating regressions. While regressions are not great, they don't "
"automatically mean a hotfix release is warranted. Unless the regressions are "
"serious and impact many users, a hotfix release is probably unnecessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:92
msgid ""
"In the end, use your best judgement and ask other maintainers for their "
"thoughts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:95
msgid "Release workflows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:97
msgid ""
"All of _Black_'s release automation uses [GitHub Actions]. All workflows are "
"therefore configured using YAML files in the `.github/workflows` directory "
"of the _Black_ repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:101
msgid "They are triggered by the publication of a [GitHub Release]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:103
msgid "Below are descriptions of our release workflows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:105
msgid "build and publish"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:107
msgid ""
"This is our main workflow. It builds an [sdist] and [wheels] to upload to "
"PyPI where the vast majority of users will download Black from. It's divided "
"into three job groups:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:110
msgid "sdist + pure wheel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:112
msgid ""
"This single job builds the sdist and pure Python wheel (i.e., a wheel that "
"only contains Python code) using [Hatch]. These artifacts are general-"
"purpose and can be used on basically any platform supported by Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:116
msgid "generate wheels matrix / mypyc wheels (…)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:118
msgid ""
"We use [mypyc] to compile _Black_ into a CPython C extension for "
"significantly improved performance. Wheels built with mypyc are platform and "
"Python version specific. [Supported platforms are documented in the FAQ]"
"(labels/mypyc-support)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:122
msgid ""
"These matrix jobs use [cibuildwheel] which handles the complicated task of "
"building C extensions for many environments for us. Since building these "
"wheels is slow, there are multiple mypyc wheels jobs (hence the term "
"\"matrix\") that build for a specific platform (as noted in the job name in "
"parentheses)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:127
msgid "publish-hatch / publish-mypyc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:129
msgid ""
"These jobs upload the built sdist and all wheels to PyPI using [Trusted "
"publishing][trusted-publishing]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:132
msgid "publish binaries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:134
msgid ""
"This workflow builds native executables for multiple platforms using "
"[PyInstaller]. This allows people to download the executable for their "
"platform and run _Black_ without a [Python runtime](https://wiki.python.org/"
"moin/PythonImplementations) installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:138
msgid ""
"The created binaries are stored on the associated GitHub Release for "
"download over _IPv4 only_ (GitHub still does not have IPv6 access 😢)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:141
msgid "docker"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:143
msgid ""
"This workflow uses the QEMU powered `buildx` feature of Docker to upload an "
"`arm64` and `amd64`/`x86_64` build of the official _Black_ Docker image™."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:146
msgid ""
"_Currently this workflow uses an API Token associated with @cooperlees "
"account_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:149
msgid "This also runs on each push to `main`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:152
msgid "post release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:154
msgid ""
"This workflow runs a few miscellaneous jobs related to repository "
"maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:156
msgid "update-stable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:158
msgid ""
"Updates the `stable` branch by force pushing it to the most recent tag. This "
"saves us from remembering to update the branch sometime after cutting the "
"release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:161
msgid "new-changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/release_process.md:163
msgid ""
"Opens a new PR to add the \"Unreleased\" section back to the changelog. The "
"PR is intentionally not auto-merged, in case there's an issue and the "
"release needs to be re-cut."
msgstr ""
